[{"id":"VR730223","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a partially submerged floating raft with a crane on it. A block is suspended from the crane and is partially submerged in the water. The bottom of the block and the bottom of the raft are at approximately the same depth below the surface of the water. An arrow labeled d sub block points from the bottom of the block to a deeper level below the water’s surface to which the crane will lower the block. The cross-sectional area of the raft is much larger than the cross-sectional area of the block that is parallel to the water’s surface.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR730223.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">At the instant shown in the figure, a raft of density <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"rho sub raft\"><math alttext=\"rho sub raft\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>ρ</mi><mtext>raft</mtext></msub></math></span></span> is floating at rest in water of density <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"rho sub water\"><math alttext=\"rho sub water\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>ρ</mi><mtext>water</mtext></msub></math></span></span>, where <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"rho sub water is greater than rho sub raft\"><math alttext=\"rho sub water is greater than rho sub raft\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>ρ</mi><mtext>water</mtext></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>ρ</mi><mtext>raft</mtext></msub></math></span></span>. A crane of negligible mass attached to the raft holds a solid block of density <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"rho sub block\"><math alttext=\"rho sub block\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>ρ</mi><mtext>block</mtext></msub></math></span></span>, where <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"rho sub block is greater than rho sub water\"><math alttext=\"rho sub block is greater than rho sub water\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>ρ</mi><mtext>block</mtext></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>ρ</mi><mtext>water</mtext></msub></math></span></span>, and the block is partially submerged in the water. The cross-sectional area of the block parallel to the surface of the water is much smaller than that of the raft. The crane then lowers the block a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"d sub block\"><math alttext=\"d sub block\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>d</mi><mtext>block</mtext></msub></math></span></span> further into the water and the raft-block system again comes to rest. After the crane lowers the block a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"d sub block\"><math alttext=\"d sub block\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>d</mi><mtext>block</mtext></msub></math></span></span>, the raft remains horizontal and has risen by an average distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"d sub raft\"><math alttext=\"d sub raft\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>d</mi><mtext>raft</mtext></msub></math></span></span>. Which of the following correctly compares <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"d sub raft\"><math alttext=\"d sub raft\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>d</mi><mtext>raft</mtext></msub></math></span></span> to <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"d sub block\"><math alttext=\"d sub block\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>d</mi><mtext>block</mtext></msub></math></span></span>, and provides a valid justification?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR730223_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"d sub raft is less than d sub block\"><math alttext=\"d sub raft is less than d sub block\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>d</mi><mtext>raft</mtext></msub><mo>&lt;</mo><msub><mi>d</mi><mtext>block</mtext></msub></math></span></span>, because the raft has a greater cross-sectional area than the block.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"d sub raft is less than d sub block\"><math alttext=\"d sub raft is less than d sub block\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>d</mi><mtext>raft</mtext></msub><mo>&lt;</mo><msub><mi>d</mi><mtext>block</mtext></msub></math></span></span>, because the density of the raft is less than that of the block.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"d sub raft equals d sub block\"><math alttext=\"d sub raft equals d sub block\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>d</mi><mtext>raft</mtext></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>d</mi><mtext>block</mtext></msub></math></span></span>, because the buoyant force on the raft is equal to that on the block.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"d sub raft equals d sub block\"><math alttext=\"d sub raft equals d sub block\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>d</mi><mtext>raft</mtext></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>d</mi><mtext>block</mtext></msub></math></span></span>, because the total volume of water displaced by the raft-block system is the same before and after the block is lowered.</p>"],"answer":0}]